This paper deals with nonmonotonic reasoning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also discusses proof-theoretic and semantic points of view, which are related to logic (cs.LO) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper uses propositional logic (cs.PL) as its basic language. Additionally, the paper discusses families of nonmonotonic consequence relations, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) as well.
